{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_724a77e437404a139f55b034","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Plan for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n     2→\n     3→## Acceptance Criteria\n     4→\n     5→- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n     6→- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n     7→- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n     8→- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n     9→- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n    10→- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n    11→\n    12→## Architecture\n    13→\n    14→### Component Overview\n    15→\n    16→1. **Session Binding Service** (NEW)\n    17→   - Manages mapping between Web session IDs and Telegram chat IDs\n    18→   - Provides API for binding/unbinding sessions\n    19→   - Persists binding state to disk\n    20→\n    21→2. **Unified Message Processor** (NEW)\n    22→   - Single entry point for both Web and Telegram messages\n    23→   - Uses `ai-cli-service.js` for execution\n    24→   - Broadcasts events via `realtime-hub.js`\n    25→\n    26→3. **SSE Event Enhancement** (MODIFY)\n    27→   - Extend `realtime-hub.js` to support cross-channel publishing\n    28→   - Add new event types: `telegram_message`, `user_message`\n    29→\n    30→4. **Telegram Bot Integration** (MODIFY)\n    31→   - Publish messages to `realtime-hub.js` when processing\n    32→   - Listen for Web-originated messages and forward to user\n    33→\n    34→## Data Flow\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→┌─────────────┐              ┌─────────────────────┐\n    38→│ Web Client  │              │  Telegram Bot       │\n    39→└──────┬──────┘              └──────────┬──────────┘\n    40→       │                                │\n    41→       │ POST /api/chat                 │ on('text')\n    42→       │ (with telegramChatId if bound) │\n    43→       ▼                                ▼\n    44→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    45→│         Session Binding Service (session-bind.js)    │\n    46→│  webSessionId <-> telegramChatId mapping             │\n    47→└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n    48→                      │\n    49→                      ▼\n    50→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    51→│      Unified Message Processor (message-router.js)   │\n    52→│  - Uses executeAiCli() for all channels             │\n    53→│  - Appends to sessionStore with unified sessionKey  │\n    54→│  - Publishes events to realtimeHub                 │\n    55→└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n    56→                      │\n    57→                      ▼\n    58→         ┌────────────────────────┐\n    59→         │  executeAiCli()        │\n    60→         │  (ai-cli-service.js)   │\n    61→         └────────┬───────────────┘\n    62→                  │\n    63→                  ▼\n    64→         ┌────────────────────────┐\n    65→         │  publish()             │\n    66→         │  realtimeHub           │\n    67→         └───────┬────────────────┘\n    68→                 │\n    69→    ┌────────────┴────────────┐\n    70→    ▼                         ▼\n    71→┌──────────┐           ┌──────────┐\n    72→│ Web SSE  │           │ Telegram │\n    73→│ Events   │           │ Forward  │\n    74→└──────────┘           └──────────┘\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→## Session Key Strategy\n    78→\n    79→- **Unified sessionKey**: `telegram:{chatId}`\n    80→- **Web session binding**: When Web client provides `telegramChatId`, use that sessionKey\n    81→- **Fallback**: If no binding, create isolated `web:{webSessionId}` session (not synced)\n    82→\n    83→## Files to Create\n    84→\n    85→1. `src/services/session-bind.js` - Session binding service\n    86→2. `src/services/message-router.js` - Unified message processor\n    87→\n    88→## Files to Modify\n    89→\n    90→1. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add binding endpoint, use message-router\n    91→2. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Publish to realtimeHub, listen for Web messages\n    92→3. `src/services/index.js` - Export new services\n    93→4. `src/services/chat-service.js` - Keep for backwards compatibility but deprecate\n    94→\n    95→## Testing Approach\n    96→\n    97→1. Unit tests for session-binding logic\n    98→2. Integration tests for Web -> Telegram sync\n    99→3. Integration tests for Telegram -> Web sync\n   100→4. Test offline reconnection scenario\n   101→\n   102→## Tasks\n   103→\n   104→### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n   105→\n   106→- [x] T1.1 Create `src/services/session-bind.js` with:\n   107→  - `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)` function\n   108→  - `unbindSession(webSessionId)` function\n   109→  - `getBoundChatId(webSessionId)` function\n   110→  - `getBoundWebSessions(telegramChatId)` function\n   111→  - Persistence to JSON file in `config.sessionPersistenceDir`\n   112→\n   113→- [x] T1.2 Create unit tests for `session-bind.js`\n   114→\n   115→- [x] T1.3 Create `src/services/message-router.js` with:\n   116→  - `processMessage({ channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId, hooks })`\n   117→  - Uses `executeAiCli()` for execution\n   118→  - Appends to sessionStore\n   119→  - Publishes events to realtimeHub for both channels\n   120→\n   121→- [x] T1.4 Create unit tests for `message-router.js`\n   122→\n   123→### Phase 2: Web Integration\n   124→\n   125→- [x] T2.1 Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js`:\n   126→  - Add POST `/api/bind` endpoint: `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)`\n   127→  - Add POST `/api/unbind` endpoint\n   128→  - Add GET `/api/bindings` endpoint to get current binding\n   129→  - Replace `chatWithSession()` with `message-router.processMessage()`\n   130→  - Pass `telegramChatId` if bound\n   131→\n   132→- [ ] T2.2 Create integration tests for binding endpoints\n   133→\n   134→- [ ] T2.3 Test Web -> Telegram message sync\n   135→\n   136→### Phase 3: Telegram Integration\n   137→\n   138→- [ ] T3.1 Modify `src/bot/telegram.js`:\n   139→  - Import `realtimeHub` and `message-router`\n   140→  - When processing text messages, publish `user_message` event with message text\n   141→  - When AI replies, publish `assistant_message` event with reply\n   142→  - Add handler for Web-originated messages (optional: forward to Telegram chat)\n   143→\n   144→- [ ] T3.2 Test Telegram -> Web SSE sync\n   145→\n   146→### Phase 4: Cross-Channel Synchronization\n   147→\n   148→- [ ] T4.1 Extend `src/services/realtime-hub.js`:\n   149→  - Add `broadcastToChannel(channel, event)` for targeted publishing\n   150→  - Add event type for cross-channel sync\n   151→\n   152→- [ ] T4.2 Implement message replay for offline Web clients:\n   153→  - SSE connection catches up with missed messages from sessionStore\n   154→\n   155→- [ ] T4.3 Test bidirectional sync with both clients online\n   156→\n   157→### Phase 5: Documentation & Cleanup\n   158→\n   159→- [ ] T5.1 Document Web-Telegram binding API\n   160→\n   161→- [ ] T5.2 Add deprecation notice to `src/services/chat-service.js`\n   162→\n   163→- [ ] T5.3 Run full integration test suite\n   164→\n   165→- [ ] T5.4 Update `.prizm-docs/` with new services\n   166→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"edf9e437-5017-45be-933b-2622d1cbfc98","uuid":"d5cd872a-14ef-4c2b-9767-e8327605a9be","timestamp":"2026-03-22T02:42:07.755Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/plan.md","content":"# Plan for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n1. **Session Binding Service** (NEW)\n   - Manages mapping between Web session IDs and Telegram chat IDs\n   - Provides API for binding/unbinding sessions\n   - Persists binding state to disk\n\n2. **Unified Message Processor** (NEW)\n   - Single entry point for both Web and Telegram messages\n   - Uses `ai-cli-service.js` for execution\n   - Broadcasts events via `realtime-hub.js`\n\n3. **SSE Event Enhancement** (MODIFY)\n   - Extend `realtime-hub.js` to support cross-channel publishing\n   - Add new event types: `telegram_message`, `user_message`\n\n4. **Telegram Bot Integration** (MODIFY)\n   - Publish messages to `realtime-hub.js` when processing\n   - Listen for Web-originated messages and forward to user\n\n## Data Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐              ┌─────────────────────┐\n│ Web Client  │              │  Telegram Bot       │\n└──────┬──────┘              └──────────┬──────────┘\n       │                                │\n       │ POST /api/chat                 │ on('text')\n       │ (with telegramChatId if bound) │\n       ▼                                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│         Session Binding Service (session-bind.js)    │\n│  webSessionId <-> telegramChatId mapping             │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│      Unified Message Processor (message-router.js)   │\n│  - Uses executeAiCli() for all channels             │\n│  - Appends to sessionStore with unified sessionKey  │\n│  - Publishes events to realtimeHub                 │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n         ┌────────────────────────┐\n         │  executeAiCli()        │\n         │  (ai-cli-service.js)   │\n         └────────┬───────────────┘\n                  │\n                  ▼\n         ┌────────────────────────┐\n         │  publish()             │\n         │  realtimeHub           │\n         └───────┬────────────────┘\n                 │\n    ┌────────────┴────────────┐\n    ▼                         ▼\n┌──────────┐           ┌──────────┐\n│ Web SSE  │           │ Telegram │\n│ Events   │           │ Forward  │\n└──────────┘           └──────────┘\n```\n\n## Session Key Strategy\n\n- **Unified sessionKey**: `telegram:{chatId}`\n- **Web session binding**: When Web client provides `telegramChatId`, use that sessionKey\n- **Fallback**: If no binding, create isolated `web:{webSessionId}` session (not synced)\n\n## Files to Create\n\n1. `src/services/session-bind.js` - Session binding service\n2. `src/services/message-router.js` - Unified message processor\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n1. `src/routes/api-routes.js` - Add binding endpoint, use message-router\n2. `src/bot/telegram.js` - Publish to realtimeHub, listen for Web messages\n3. `src/services/index.js` - Export new services\n4. `src/services/chat-service.js` - Keep for backwards compatibility but deprecate\n\n## Testing Approach\n\n1. Unit tests for session-binding logic\n2. Integration tests for Web -> Telegram sync\n3. Integration tests for Telegram -> Web sync\n4. Test offline reconnection scenario\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure\n\n- [x] T1.1 Create `src/services/session-bind.js` with:\n  - `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)` function\n  - `unbindSession(webSessionId)` function\n  - `getBoundChatId(webSessionId)` function\n  - `getBoundWebSessions(telegramChatId)` function\n  - Persistence to JSON file in `config.sessionPersistenceDir`\n\n- [x] T1.2 Create unit tests for `session-bind.js`\n\n- [x] T1.3 Create `src/services/message-router.js` with:\n  - `processMessage({ channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId, hooks })`\n  - Uses `executeAiCli()` for execution\n  - Appends to sessionStore\n  - Publishes events to realtimeHub for both channels\n\n- [x] T1.4 Create unit tests for `message-router.js`\n\n### Phase 2: Web Integration\n\n- [x] T2.1 Modify `src/routes/api-routes.js`:\n  - Add POST `/api/bind` endpoint: `bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId)`\n  - Add POST `/api/unbind` endpoint\n  - Add GET `/api/bindings` endpoint to get current binding\n  - Replace `chatWithSession()` with `message-router.processMessage()`\n  - Pass `telegramChatId` if bound\n\n- [ ] T2.2 Create integration tests for binding endpoints\n\n- [ ] T2.3 Test Web -> Telegram message sync\n\n### Phase 3: Telegram Integration\n\n- [ ] T3.1 Modify `src/bot/telegram.js`:\n  - Import `realtimeHub` and `message-router`\n  - When processing text messages, publish `user_message` event with message text\n  - When AI replies, publish `assistant_message` event with reply\n  - Add handler for Web-originated messages (optional: forward to Telegram chat)\n\n- [ ] T3.2 Test Telegram -> Web SSE sync\n\n### Phase 4: Cross-Channel Synchronization\n\n- [ ] T4.1 Extend `src/services/realtime-hub.js`:\n  - Add `broadcastToChannel(channel, event)` for targeted publishing\n  - Add event type for cross-channel sync\n\n- [ ] T4.2 Implement message replay for offline Web clients:\n  - SSE connection catches up with missed messages from sessionStore\n\n- [ ] T4.3 Test bidirectional sync with both clients online\n\n### Phase 5: Documentation & Cleanup\n\n- [ ] T5.1 Document Web-Telegram binding API\n\n- [ ] T5.2 Add deprecation notice to `src/services/chat-service.js`\n\n- [ ] T5.3 Run full integration test suite\n\n- [ ] T5.4 Update `.prizm-docs/` with new services\n","numLines":166,"startLine":1,"totalLines":166}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_cb4841c365624606b107c486","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Context Snapshot for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n     2→\n     3→## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n     4→\n     5→**Feature Description (from context):**\n     6→\n     7→Web 页面与 Telegram 共享同一会话，消息双向实时同步。当前 Web 端使用独立的 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，Telegram 端使用 ai-cli-service.js，两套系统完全隔离。\n     8→\n     9→统一架构：将 Web 端和 Telegram 端的消息路由统一到同一个 session store 和 AI CLI 执行引擎（ai-cli-service.js）；废弃或重构 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，使 Web 端也通过 ai-cli-service 执行；统一 session key 映射策略，让 Web 和 Telegram 可以关联到同一个会话。\n    10→\n    11→实时同步：Telegram 端收到的消息和回复实时通过 SSE 推送到 Web 页面；Web 端发送的消息同步转发到 Telegram 对话并在 Bot 中执行；双端同时在线时，两边都能看到完整的对话流。\n    12→\n    13→会话绑定：提供会话绑定机制（如 Web 页面输入 Telegram chat ID 或扫码绑定），确保 Web 连接到正确的 Telegram 会话。\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n    18→- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n    19→- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n    20→- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n    21→- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n    22→- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n    23→\n    24→## Dependencies (Already Completed)\n    25→\n    26→- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n    27→- F-013 - Session and Context Manager (completed)\n    28→\n    29→---\n    30→\n    31→## Section 2 — Project Structure\n    32→\n    33→Top-level directories:\n    34→```\n    35→src/\n    36→├── adapters/        - External service adapters (codebuddy.js)\n    37→├── bot/             - Telegram bot implementation\n    38→├── http/            - HTTP server with SSE\n    39→├── pipeline-infra/  - Dev pipeline execution framework\n    40→├── routes/          - HTTP API endpoints\n    41→├── security/        - Security and permission enforcement\n    42→├── services/        - Core business logic (ai-cli-service.js, chat-service.js, session-store.js, realtime-hub.js)\n    43→└── utils/           - Utility functions\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n    49→\n    50→### root.prizm (L0):\n    51→```\n    52→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n    53→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n    54→LANG: nodejs\n    55→MODULE_INDEX:\n    56→- src/bot: bot.prizm\n    57→- src/http: http.prizm\n    58→- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n    59→- src/routes: routes.prizm\n    60→- src/security: security.prizm\n    61→- src/services: services.prizm\n    62→- src/utils: utils.prizm\n    63→- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\n    64→RULES:\n    65→- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n    66→- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n    67→- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n    68→- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n    69→- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n    70→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→### src/services.prizm (L1):\n    74→```\n    75→MODULE: src/services\n    76→FILES: index.js, ai-cli-service.js, alert-manager-service.js, alias-store.js, audit-log-service.js, backend-registry.js, chat-queue.js, chat-service.js, command-executor-service.js, commit-service.js, config-service.js, file-service.js, file-watcher-service.js, git-service.js, log-pager.js, output-pager-service.js, pipeline-control-service.js, pipeline-controller.js, plan-ingestion-service.js, realtime-hub.js, scheduled-task-service.js, screenshot-service.js, session-context-service.js, session-store.js, status-aggregator.js, system-exec-service.js, system-monitor-service.js, telegram-pusher.js\n    77→RESPONSIBILITY: Core business logic and state management\n    78→INTERFACES:\n    79→- ai-cli-service: executeAICLI(message, chatId)\n    80→- session-store: get(chatId), set(chatId, data)\n    81→- realtime-hub: broadcast(event, data)\n    82→- chat-service: processMessage(message, session)\n    83→DEPENDENCIES:\n    84→- uses: pino: Logging\n    85→- uses: zod: Validation\n    86→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    87→```\n    88→\n    89→---\n    90→\n    91→## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n    92→\n    93→### src/services/chat-service.js (80 lines):\n    94→```javascript\n    95→import { runCodeBuddy } from '../adapters/codebuddy.js';\n    96→import { sanitizeInput } from '../security/guard.js';\n    97→import { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\n    98→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n    99→\n   100→export function buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId) {\n   101→  const normalizedChannel = String(channel ?? '').trim();\n   102→  const normalizedSessionId = String(sessionId ?? '').trim();\n   103→\n   104→  if (!normalizedChannel) {\n   105→    throw new Error('channel 不能为空。');\n   106→  }\n   107→\n   108→  if (!normalizedSessionId) {\n   109→    throw new Error('sessionId 不能为空。');\n   110→  }\n   111→\n   112→  return {\n   113→    channel: normalizedChannel,\n   114→    sessionId: normalizedSessionId,\n   115→    sessionKey: `${normalizedChannel}:${normalizedSessionId}`\n   116→  };\n   117→}\n   118→\n   119→/**\n   120→ * @param {Object} params\n   121→ * @param {string} params.channel\n   122→ * @param {string} params.sessionId\n   123→ * @param {string} params.message\n   124→ * @param {{ onStatus?: Function, onAssistantChunk?: Function, onAssistantDone?: Function }} [params.realtimeHooks]\n   125→ */\n   126→export async function chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks = {} }) {\n   127→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   128→\n   129→  return chatQueue.run(session.sessionKey, async () => {\n   130→    const sanitized = sanitizeInput(message);\n   131→\n   132→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n   133→      stage: 'accepted',\n   134→      channel: session.channel,\n   135→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   136→    });\n   137→\n   138→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'user', sanitized);\n   139→\n   140→    const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(session.sessionKey, session.channel);\n   141→\n   142→    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n   143→      stage: 'running',\n   144→      channel: session.channel,\n   145→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   146→    });\n   147→\n   148→    const reply = await runCodeBuddy(prompt, {\n   149→      onStdoutChunk: (text) => {\n   150→        realtimeHooks.onAssistantChunk?.({\n   151→          text,\n   152→          channel: session.channel,\n   153→          sessionId: session.sessionId\n   154→        });\n   155→      }\n   156→    });\n   157→\n   158→    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'assistant', reply);\n   159→\n   160→    realtimeHooks.onAssistantDone?.({\n   161→      reply,\n   162→      channel: session.channel,\n   163→      sessionId: session.sessionId\n   164→    });\n   165→\n   166→    return reply;\n   167→  });\n   168→}\n   169→\n   170→export function resetSession({ channel, sessionId }) {\n   171→  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   172→  sessionStore.clear(session.sessionKey);\n   173→}\n   174→```\n   175→\n   176→### src/adapters/codebuddy.js (120 lines):\n   177→```javascript\n   178→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n   179→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   180→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n   181→\n   182→function writeEcho(tag, text) {\n   183→  const normalized = String(text ?? '');\n   184→  if (!normalized) {\n   185→    return;\n   186→  }\n   187→\n   188→  const lines = normalized.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n   189→  for (const line of lines) {\n   190→    if (!line) {\n   191→      continue;\n   192→    }\n   193→    process.stdout.write(`[CodeBuddy:${tag}] ${line}\\n`);\n   194→  }\n   195→}\n   196→\n   197→export async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n   198→  const { onStdoutChunk } = options;\n   199→  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n   200→\n   201→  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n   202→    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n   206→    const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n   207→      stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n   208→    });\n   209→\n   210→    const startedAt = Date.now();\n   211→    logger.info({ pid: child.pid, bin: config.codebuddyBin, args }, 'CodeBuddy process started');\n   212→\n   213→    let stdout = '';\n   214→    let stderr = '';\n   215→\n   216→    const heartbeat =\n   217→      config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs > 0\n   218→        ? setInterval(() => {\n   219→            const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   220→            logger.info(\n   221→              {\n   222→                pid: child.pid,\n   223→                elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000),\n   224→                stdoutBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stdout),\n   225→                stderrBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stderr)\n   226→              },\n   227→              'CodeBuddy still running'\n   228→            );\n   229→          }, config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs)\n   230→        : null;\n   231→\n   232→    const timeout =\n   233→      config.requestTimeoutMs > 0\n   234→        ? setTimeout(() => {\n   235→            child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   236→            reject(new Error(`CodeBuddy 执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）`));\n   237→          }, config.requestTimeoutMs)\n   238→        : null;\n   239→\n   240→    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   241→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   242→      stdout += text;\n   243→\n   244→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   245→        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n   246→      }\n   247→\n   248→      if (typeof onStdoutChunk === 'function') {\n   249→        onStdoutChunk(text);\n   250→      }\n   251→    });\n   252→\n   253→    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   254→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   255→      stderr += text;\n   256→\n   257→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   258→        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n   259→      }\n   260→    });\n   261→\n   262→    child.on('error', (err) => {\n   263→      if (timeout) {\n   264→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   265→      }\n   266→      if (heartbeat) {\n   267→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   268→      }\n   269→      reject(new Error(`无法启动 CodeBuddy: ${err.message}`));\n   270→    });\n   271→\n   272→    child.on('close', (code) => {\n   273→      if (timeout) {\n   274→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   275→      }\n   276→      if (heartbeat) {\n   277→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   278→      }\n   279→\n   280→      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   281→      logger.info(\n   282→        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000) },\n   283→        'CodeBuddy process closed'\n   284→      );\n   285→\n   286→      if (code === 0) {\n   287→        resolve(stdout.trim() || 'CodeBuddy 未返回文本结果。');\n   288→        return;\n   289→      }\n   290→\n   291→      reject(\n   292→        new Error(`CodeBuddy 退出码 ${code}。${stderr ? `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}` : ''}`)\n   293→      );\n   294→    });\n   295→  });\n   296→}\n   297→```\n   298→\n   299→### src/services/ai-cli-service.js (564 lines):\n   300→```javascript\n   301→// Key interface: executeAiCli({ sessionId, prompt, hooks, signal, timeoutMs, ... })\n   302→// Returns: Promise<{ output, timedOut, interrupted, elapsedMs, exitCode, stderr }>\n   303→// Hooks: onChunk(text), onHeartbeat(info), onStatus(status)\n   304→\n   305→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n   306→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   307→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n   308→import { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n   309→import { backendRegistry as defaultBackendRegistry } from './backend-registry.js';\n   310→import { createHeartbeatManager } from '../utils/heartbeat-manager.js';\n   311→\n   312→// Allow dependency injection for testing\n   313→let backendRegistry = defaultBackendRegistry;\n   314→\n   315→// ... metrics functions ...\n   316→\n   317→/**\n   318→ * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n   319→ * @property {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n   320→ * @property {string} prompt - User prompt/input\n   321→ * @property {string} [userId] - User ID who initiated the task (for permission checks)\n   322→ * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n   323→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback (text: string) => void\n   324→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback (info: HeartbeatInfo) => void\n   325→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (status: string) => void\n   326→ * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Optional abort signal\n   327→ * @property {number} [timeoutMs] - Optional timeout override\n   328→ * @property {number} [heartbeatThresholdMs] - Heartbeat threshold override\n   329→ * @property {number} [heartbeatIntervalMs] - Heartbeat interval override\n   330→ * @property {string} [bin] - Optional binary override (for testing)\n   331→ * @property {string[]} [args] - Optional args override (for testing, replaces default args)\n   332→ */\n   333→\n   334→export async function executeAiCli(options) {\n   335→  const {\n   336→    sessionId,\n   337→    prompt,\n   338→    userId,\n   339→    hooks = {},\n   340→    signal,\n   341→    timeoutMs,\n   342→    heartbeatThresholdMs,\n   343→    heartbeatIntervalMs,\n   344→    bin,\n   345→    args: customArgs\n   346→  } = options;\n   347→\n   348→  // Get session-specific backend or use default\n   349→  const sessionBackendName = sessionStore.getCurrentBackend(sessionId);\n   350→  const sessionBackend = sessionBackendName ? backendRegistry.getBackend(sessionBackendName) : null;\n   351→  const effectiveBin = bin || (sessionBackend?.binPath) || config.codebuddyBin;\n   352→  const effectiveTimeoutMs = timeoutMs ?? config.requestTimeoutMs;\n   353→  const effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs = heartbeatThresholdMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs;\n   354→  const effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs = heartbeatIntervalMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs;\n   355→  const enableHeartbeat = config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat;\n   356→\n   357→  // Validate backend binary exists if using session backend\n   358→  if (sessionBackendName && !backendRegistry.validateBackend(sessionBackendName)) {\n   359→    const defaultBackend = backendRegistry.getDefaultBackend();\n   360→    const fallbackBin = defaultBackend?.binPath || config.codebuddyBin;\n   361→\n   362→    logger.warn(`Backend \"${sessionBackendName}\" not accessible, falling back to default`);\n   363→\n   364→    // Reset to default backend for this session\n   365→    sessionStore.resetBackend(sessionId);\n   366→\n   367→    return {\n   368→      output: `⚠️ 后端 \"${sessionBackendName}\" 不可用，已切换回默认后端。\\n建议：检查后端配置或使用 /cli reset 重置。`,\n   369→      timedOut: false,\n   370→      interrupted: false,\n   371→      elapsedMs: 0,\n   372→      exitCode: null,\n   373→      stderr: ''\n   374→    };\n   375→  }\n   376→\n   377→  // Use custom args if provided (for testing), otherwise build default args\n   378→  const args = customArgs ?? (() => {\n   379→    const defaultArgs = ['-p', prompt];\n   380→    // Use session backend's permission flag if available, otherwise fallback to config\n   381→    const permissionFlag = sessionBackend?.permissionFlag || config.codebuddyPermissionFlag;\n   382→    if (permissionFlag) {\n   383→      defaultArgs.push(permissionFlag);\n   384→    }\n   385→    return defaultArgs;\n   386→  })();\n   387→\n   388→  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n   389→    let stdout = '';\n   390→    let stderr = '';\n   391→    let stdoutBytes = 0;\n   392→    let interrupted = false;\n   393→    let timedOut = false;\n   394→    const startedAt = Date.now();\n   395→    const sessionKey = sessionId;\n   396→\n   397→    // Heartbeat manager\n   398→    const heartbeatManager = createHeartbeatManager();\n   399→\n   400→    // Spawn process\n   401→    let child;\n   402→    try {\n   403→      child = spawn(effectiveBin, args, {\n   404→        stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n   405→      });\n   406→    } catch (err) {\n   407→      resolve({\n   408→        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n   409→        timedOut: false,\n   410→        interrupted: false,\n   411→        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n   412→        exitCode: null,\n   413→        stderr: ''\n   414→      });\n   415→      return;\n   416→    }\n   417→\n   418→    // Track process in session store\n   419→    sessionStore.setActiveProcess(sessionKey, {\n   420→      pid: child.pid,\n   421→      startedAt,\n   422→      childProcess: child,\n   423→      interrupted: false,\n   424→      timedOut: false,\n   425→      userId\n   426→    });\n   427→\n   428→    logger.info({\n   429→    pid: child.pid,\n   430→    bin: effectiveBin,\n   431→    backend: sessionBackendName || 'default',\n   432→    args,\n   433→    sessionId\n   434→  }, 'AI CLI process started');\n   435→\n   436→    // Handle process error\n   437→    child.on('error', (err) => {\n   438→      cleanup();\n   439→      resolve({\n   440→        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n   441→        timedOut: false,\n   442→        interrupted: false,\n   443→        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n   444→        exitCode: null,\n   445→        stderr\n   446→      });\n   447→    });\n   448→\n   449→    // Handle stdout\n   450→    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   451→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   452→      stdout += text;\n   453→      stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(text);\n   454→\n   455→      // Update session store byte count\n   456→      sessionStore.updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, Buffer.byteLength(text));\n   457→\n   458→      // Echo to console if enabled\n   459→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   460→        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n   461→      }\n   462→\n   463→      // Call onChunk hook\n   464→      if (typeof hooks.onChunk === 'function') {\n   465→        hooks.onChunk(text);\n   466→      }\n   467→    });\n   468→\n   469→    // Handle stderr\n   470→    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n   471→      const text = chunk.toString();\n   472→      stderr += text;\n   473→\n   474→      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n   475→        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n   476→      }\n   477→    });\n   478→\n   479→    // Timeout handler\n   480→    const timeout = effectiveTimeoutMs > 0\n   481→      ? setTimeout(() => {\n   482→          timedOut = true;\n   483→          const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   484→          if (info) {\n   485→            info.timedOut = true;\n   486→          }\n   487→          child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   488→\n   489→          // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n   490→          setTimeout(() => {\n   491→            if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n   492→              child.kill('SIGKILL');\n   493→            }\n   494→          }, 5000);\n   495→        }, effectiveTimeoutMs)\n   496→      : null;\n   497→\n   498→    // Abort signal handler\n   499→    const onAbort = () => {\n   500→      interrupted = true;\n   501→      const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   502→      if (info) {\n   503→        info.interrupted = true;\n   504→      }\n   505→      child.kill('SIGTERM');\n   506→\n   507→      // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n   508→      setTimeout(() => {\n   509→        if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n   510→          child.kill('SIGKILL');\n   511→        }\n   512→      }, 5000);\n   513→    };\n   514→\n   515→    if (signal) {\n   516→      signal.addEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n   517→    }\n   518→\n   519→    // Heartbeat setup\n   520→    if (enableHeartbeat && typeof hooks.onHeartbeat === 'function') {\n   521→      heartbeatManager.start({\n   522→        callback: () => {\n   523→          const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   524→          hooks.onHeartbeat({\n   525→            elapsedMs,\n   526→            stdoutBytes,\n   527→            status: 'running'\n   528→          });\n   529→        },\n   530→        intervalMs: effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs,\n   531→        thresholdMs: effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs\n   532→      });\n   533→    }\n   534→\n   535→    // Cleanup function\n   536→    function cleanup() {\n   537→      if (timeout) {\n   538→        clearTimeout(timeout);\n   539→      }\n   540→      heartbeatManager.stop();\n   541→      sessionStore.clearActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   542→      if (signal) {\n   543→        signal.removeEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n   544→      }\n   545→    }\n   546→\n   547→    // Handle process close\n   548→    child.on('close', (code) => {\n   549→      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n   550→\n   551→      // Check interrupted/timedOut flags from session store (may be set by interruptAiCli)\n   552→      const storedInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n   553→      if (storedInfo) {\n   554→        if (storedInfo.interrupted) {\n   555→          interrupted = true;\n   556→        }\n   557→        if (storedInfo.timedOut) {\n   558→          timedOut = true;\n   559→        }\n   560→      }\n   561→\n   562→      cleanup();\n   563→\n   564→      logger.info(\n   565→        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000), sessionId },\n   566→        'AI CLI process closed'\n   567→      );\n   568→\n   569→      // Build output\n   570→      let output = stdout.trim();\n   571→\n   572→      if (interrupted) {\n   573→        output = output || '任务已被用户中断。';\n   574→      } else if (timedOut) {\n   575→        output = output || `任务执行超时（>${effectiveTimeoutMs}ms）。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`;\n   576→      } else if (code !== 0) {\n   577→        output = output || `AI CLI 退出码 ${code}。`;\n   578→        if (stderr.trim()) {\n   579→          output += `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}`;\n   580→        }\n   581→      }\n   582→\n   583→      // Record metrics (T-051)\n   584→      recordMetrics({\n   585→        elapsedMs,\n   586→        stdoutBytes,\n   587→        success: code === 0 && !interrupted && !timedOut,\n   588→        timedOut,\n   589→        interrupted\n   590→      });\n   591→\n   592→      resolve({\n   593→        output: output || 'AI CLI 未返回文本结果。',\n   594→        timedOut,\n   595→        interrupted,\n   596→        elapsedMs,\n   597→        exitCode: code,\n   598→        stderr: stderr.trim()\n   599→      });\n   600→    });\n   601→  });\n   602→}\n   603→\n   604→export function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {\n   605→  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   606→\n   607→  if (!processInfo) {\n   608→    return { ok: false, error: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n   609→  }\n   610→\n   611→  const { pid, childProcess } = processInfo;\n   612→\n   613→  try {\n   614→    // Mark as interrupted so close handler knows\n   615→    processInfo.interrupted = true;\n   616→\n   617→    // Send SIGTERM first\n   618→    childProcess.kill('SIGTERM');\n   619→\n   620→    // Schedule SIGKILL as backup\n   621→    setTimeout(() => {\n   622→      const stillRunning = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   623→      if (stillRunning) {\n   624→        try {\n   625→          childProcess.kill('SIGKILL');\n   626→        } catch {\n   627→          // Process already dead\n   628→        }\n   629→      }\n   630→    }, 5000);\n   631→\n   632→    logger.info({ pid, sessionId }, 'AI CLI process interrupted');\n   633→\n   634→    return { ok: true, pid };\n   635→  } catch (err) {\n   636→    return { ok: false, error: `中断失败: ${err.message}` };\n   637→  }\n   638→}\n   639→\n   640→export function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {\n   641→  return sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId) !== null;\n   642→}\n   643→\n   644→export function getActiveProcessInfo(sessionId) {\n   645→  const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   646→  if (!info) {\n   647→    return null;\n   648→  }\n   649→\n   650→  // Don't expose childProcess to external callers\n   651→  return {\n   652→    pid: info.pid,\n   653→    startedAt: info.startedAt,\n   654→    stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0,\n   655→    userId: info.userId\n   656→  };\n   657→}\n   658→\n   659→export function canInterruptAiCli(sessionId, requestUserId, isAdminFn) {\n   660→  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n   661→\n   662→  if (!processInfo) {\n   663→    return { canInterrupt: false, reason: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n   664→  }\n   665→\n   666→  // Admin can always interrupt\n   667→  if (isAdminFn && isAdminFn(requestUserId)) {\n   668→    return { canInterrupt: true };\n   669→  }\n   670→\n   671→  // Task owner can interrupt\n   672→  const taskUserId = processInfo.userId;\n   673→  if (taskUserId && String(taskUserId) === String(requestUserId)) {\n   674→    return { canInterrupt: true };\n   675→  }\n   676→\n   677→  // Otherwise, permission denied\n   678→  return {\n   679→    canInterrupt: false,\n   680→    reason: '权限不足。只有任务发起者或管理员可以中断任务。'\n   681→  };\n   682→}\n   683→```\n   684→\n   685→### src/services/session-store.js (427 lines):\n   686→```javascript\n   687→import { config } from '../config.js';\n   688→\n   689→class SessionStore {\n   690→  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   691→  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n   692→  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n   693→  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n   694→  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   695→  // F-010: File search results state for pagination\n   696→  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n   697→  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking\n   698→  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n   699→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n   700→  #commandHistoryBySessionKey = new Map();\n   701→  #envOverridesBySessionKey = new Map();\n   702→  #lastActivityBySessionKey = new Map();\n   703→  #userIdBySessionKey = new Map();\n   704→  #sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey = new Map();\n   705→  // F-015: AI CLI Backend Switcher\n   706→  #currentBackendBySessionKey = new Map();\n   707→\n   708→  get(sessionKey) {\n   709→    if (!this.#messagesBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n   710→      this.#messagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n   711→    }\n   712→    return this.#messagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   713→  }\n   714→\n   715→  append(sessionKey, role, content) {\n   716→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n   717→    messages.push({ role, content });\n   718→\n   719→    const maxMessages = config.maxHistoryTurns * 2;\n   720→    if (messages.length > maxMessages) {\n   721→      messages.splice(0, messages.length - maxMessages);\n   722→    }\n   723→  }\n   724→\n   725→  clear(sessionKey) {\n   726→    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   727→    this.#commitsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   728→    // F-009: Clear cwd and output pages\n   729→    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   730→    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   731→    // F-010: Clear search results\n   732→    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   733→    // F-011: Clear active process\n   734→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   735→    // F-013: Clear session context data\n   736→    this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   737→    this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   738→    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   739→    this.#userIdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   740→    this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   741→    // F-015: Clear backend selection\n   742→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   743→  }\n   744→\n   745→  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel = 'unknown') {\n   746→    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n   747→\n   748→    return [\n   749→      `你正在通过 ${channel} 渠道提供电脑助手服务。`,\n   750→      '请使用自然、简洁、可执行的表达。',\n   751→      '如果用户请求系统操作或截图，明确说明步骤与结果。',\n   752→      '当你产出本地文件（截图/文档）时，必须额外输出独立行：SEND_FILE:<绝对路径>。',\n   753→      '禁止仅输出 @image:xxx 或相对路径；路径必须是绝对路径（例如 /var/folders/... 或 /home/...）。',\n   754→      '以下是最近对话上下文：',\n   755→      ...messages.map((msg) => `${msg.role === 'user' ? '用户' : '助手'}: ${msg.content}`),\n   756→      '请继续回答最后一条用户消息。'\n   757→    ].join('\\n');\n   758→  }\n   759→  // ... other methods for commits, cwd, output, search results, active process, command history, env overrides, session tracking, etc.\n   760→\n   761→  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking methods\n   762→  getActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n   763→    return this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n   764→  }\n   765→\n   766→  setActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) {\n   767→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, {\n   768→      ...info,\n   769→      stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0\n   770→    });\n   771→  }\n   772→\n   773→  updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) {\n   774→    const info = this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   775→    if (info) {\n   776→      info.stdoutBytes = (info.stdoutBytes ?? 0) + bytes;\n   777→    }\n   778→  }\n   779→\n   780→  clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n   781→    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   782→  }\n   783→\n   784→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager methods\n   785→  touchSession(sessionKey, userId) {\n   786→    const now = Date.now();\n   787→    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n   788→    if (userId !== undefined) {\n   789→      this.#userIdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, userId);\n   790→    }\n   791→    // Set creation time if this is a new session\n   792→    if (!this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n   793→      this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n   794→    }\n   795→  }\n   796→\n   797→  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) {\n   798→    const userId = this.#userIdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   799→    const createdAt = this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   800→    const lastActivityAt = this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n   801→\n   802→    // Return null if session has no tracking data\n   803→    if (!createdAt && !lastActivityAt) {\n   804→      return null;\n   805→    }\n   806→\n   807→    return {\n   808→      sessionKey,\n   809→      userId: userId || null,\n   810→      cwd: this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null,\n   811→      envOverrides: { ...this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) } || {},\n   812→      commandCount: (this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || []).length,\n   813→      createdAt: createdAt || null,\n   814→      lastActivityAt: lastActivityAt || null,\n   815→      // F-015: Add backend information\n   816→      currentBackend: this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null\n   817→    };\n   818→  }\n   819→\n   820→  getAllSessionKeys() {\n   821→    // Return keys from sessions that have activity tracking\n   822→    return Array.from(this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.keys());\n   823→  }\n   824→\n   825→  getCurrentBackend(sessionKey) {\n   826→    return this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n   827→  }\n   828→\n   829→  setCurrentBackend(sessionKey, backendName) {\n   830→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, backendName);\n   831→  }\n   832→\n   833→  resetBackend(sessionKey) {\n   834→    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n   835→  }\n   836→}\n   837→\n   838→export const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n   839→export { SessionStore };\n   840→```\n   841→\n   842→### src/services/realtime-hub.js (35 lines):\n   843→```javascript\n   844→class RealtimeHub {\n   845→  #listenersBySession = new Map();\n   846→\n   847→  subscribe(sessionKey, listener) {\n   848→    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey) ?? new Set();\n   849→    listeners.add(listener);\n   850→    this.#listenersBySession.set(sessionKey, listeners);\n   851→\n   852→    return () => {\n   853→      const current = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n   854→      if (!current) {\n   855→        return;\n   856→      }\n   857→\n   858→      current.delete(listener);\n   859→      if (current.size === 0) {\n   860→        this.#listenersBySession.delete(sessionKey);\n   861→      }\n   862→    };\n   863→  }\n   864→\n   865→  publish(sessionKey, event) {\n   866→    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n   867→    if (!listeners || listeners.size === 0) {\n   868→      return;\n   869→    }\n   870→\n   871→    for (const listener of listeners) {\n   872→      listener(event);\n   873→    }\n   874→  }\n   875→}\n   876→\n   877→export const realtimeHub = new RealtimeHub();\n   878→```\n   879→\n   880→### src/routes/api-routes.js (106 lines):\n   881→```javascript\n   882→import { Router } from 'express';\n   883→import { buildSessionContext, chatWithSession, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\n   884→import { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\n   885→import { executeSystemCommand } from '../services/system-exec-service.js';\n   886→\n   887→function writeSseEvent(res, event, payload) {\n   888→  res.write(`event: ${event}\\n`);\n   889→  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n\\n`);\n   890→}\n   891→\n   892→export function createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }) {\n   893→  const router = Router();\n   894→\n   895→  router.get('/events', (req, res, next) => {\n   896→    try {\n   897→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.query;\n   898→      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   899→\n   900→      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');\n   901→      res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');\n   902→      res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');\n   903→      res.flushHeaders?.();\n   904→\n   905→      writeSseEvent(res, 'connected', {\n   906→        ok: true,\n   907→        channel: session.channel,\n   908→        sessionId: session.sessionId\n   909→      });\n   910→\n   911→      const unsubscribe = realtimeHub.subscribe(session.sessionKey, (event) => {\n   912→        writeSseEvent(res, event.type, event.payload);\n   913→      });\n   914→\n   915→      const heartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n   916→        res.write(': ping\\n\\n');\n   917→      }, 20000);\n   918→\n   919→      req.on('close', () => {\n   920→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   921→        unsubscribe();\n   922→      });\n   923→    } catch (error) {\n   924→      next(error);\n   925→    }\n   926→  });\n   927→\n   928→  router.post('/chat', async (req, res, next) => {\n   929→    try {\n   930→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, message } = req.body ?? {};\n   931→      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n   932→\n   933→      const reply = await chatWithSession({\n   934→        channel,\n   935→        sessionId,\n   936→        message,\n   937→        realtimeHooks: {\n   938→          onStatus: (payload) => {\n   939→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'status', payload });\n   940→          },\n   941→          onAssistantChunk: (payload) => {\n   942→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_chunk', payload });\n   943→          },\n   944→          onAssistantDone: (payload) => {\n   945→            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_done', payload });\n   946→          }\n   947→        }\n   948→      });\n   949→\n   950→      res.json({ ok: true, reply });\n   951→    } catch (error) {\n   952→      next(error);\n   953→    }\n   954→  });\n   955→\n   956→  router.post('/chat/reset', async (req, res, next) => {\n   957→    try {\n   958→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.body ?? {};\n   959→      resetSession({ channel, sessionId });\n   960→      res.json({ ok: true });\n   961→    } catch (error) {\n   962→      next(error);\n   963→    }\n   964→  });\n   965→\n   966→  return router;\n   967→}\n   968→```\n   969→\n   970→### src/http/server.js (25 lines):\n   971→```javascript\n   972→import express from 'express';\n   973→import { createApiRouter } from '../routes/api-routes.js';\n   974→import { realtimeHub } from '../services/realtime-hub.js';\n   975→\n   976→export function createHttpServer({ logger }) {\n   977→  const app = express();\n   978→\n   979→  app.use(express.json({ limit: '2mb' }));\n   980→\n   981→  app.get('/healthz', (_req, res) => {\n   982→    res.json({ ok: true });\n   983→  });\n   984→\n   985→  app.use('/api', createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }));\n   986→  app.use(express.static('public'));\n   987→\n   988→  app.use((error, _req, res, _next) => {\n   989→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   990→    logger.error({ err: message }, 'HTTP request failed');\n   991→    res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: message });\n   992→  });\n   993→\n   994→  return app;\n   995→}\n   996→```\n   997→\n   998→### src/bot/telegram.js (partial - key sections related to chat handling):\n   999→```javascript\n  1000→// Key parts for context\n  1001→\n  1002→function buildSessionId(ctx) {\n  1003→  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n  1004→}\n  1005→\n  1006→// Bot uses ai-cli-service for execution:\n  1007→const result = await executeAiCli({\n  1008→  sessionId,\n  1009→  prompt,\n  1010→  hooks: {\n  1011→    onChunk: (text) => {\n  1012→      streamPublisher.push(text);\n  1013→    },\n  1014→    onHeartbeat: config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat ? (info) => {\n  1015→      // Send/update heartbeat progress message\n  1016→      const elapsedSec = Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000);\n  1017→      const progressText = `⏳ 任务执行中... (${elapsedSec}s, ${Math.floor(info.stdoutBytes / 1024)}KB)`;\n  1018→\n  1019→      // Don't await - fire and forget\n  1020→      if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n  1021→        ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id, undefined, progressText)\n  1022→          .catch(() => {});\n  1023→      } else {\n  1024→        ctx.reply(progressText)\n  1025→          .then((msg) => { lastHeartbeatMsg = msg; })\n  1026→          .catch(() => {});\n  1027→      }\n  1028→    } : undefined,\n  1029→    onStatus: (status) => {\n  1030→      if (status === 'running') {\n  1031→        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n  1032→      }\n  1033→    }\n  1034→  }\n  1035→});\n  1036→\n  1037→// Session key format: `telegram:${sessionId}`\n  1038→const sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n  1039→\n  1040→// Append user message to session history\n  1041→sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', ctx.message.text);\n  1042→\n  1043→// Append assistant reply to session history\n  1044→sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', result.output);\n  1045→```\n  1046→\n  1047→---\n  1048→\n  1049→## Section 5 — Integration Points\n  1050→\n  1051→### Current Flow:\n  1052→\n  1053→**Web Path:**\n  1054→1. POST /api/chat with message\n  1055→2. buildSessionContext() → sessionKey = \"web:<sessionId>\"\n  1056→3. chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() (via adapter)\n  1057→4. Uses realtimeHub.publish() for SSE\n  1058→\n  1059→**Telegram Path:**\n  1060→1. bot.on('text') receives message\n  1061→2. buildSessionId() → uses ctx.chat.id\n  1062→3. sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\"\n  1063→4. executeAiCli() directly\n  1064→5. Messages appended to sessionStore using sessionKey\n  1065→\n  1066→### Key Problem:\n  1067→- Web and Telegram use different execution engines (codebuddy vs ai-cli)\n  1068→- Session keys are isolated per channel (web:123 vs telegram:123)\n  1069→- No cross-channel message synchronization\n  1070→\n  1071→---\n  1072→\n  1073→## Section 6 — Data Flow Diagram\n  1074→\n  1075→```\n  1076→Web Client\n  1077→  │ POST /api/chat\n  1078→  ▼\n  1079→api-routes.js → chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() → sessionKey=\"web:id\"\n  1080→                                            │\n  1081→                                            ▼\n  1082→                                    session-store (isolated)\n  1083→\n  1084→Telegram Bot\n  1085→  │ on('text')\n  1086→  ▼\n  1087→telegram.js → executeAiCli() → sessionKey=\"telegram:id\"\n  1088→                            │\n  1089→                            ▼\n  1090→                        session-store (isolated)\n  1091→```\n  1092→\n  1093→### Target Flow:\n  1094→\n  1095→```\n  1096→Web Client          Telegram Bot\n  1097→  │                      │\n  1098→  ▼                      │\n  1099→Session Key = telegram:<chatId> (bound)\n  1100→  │                      │\n  1101→  ├──────────────────────┤\n  1102→  │                      │\n  1103→  ▼                      ▼\n  1104→executeAiCli()    executeAiCli()\n  1105→  │                      │\n  1106→  └──────────────────────┘\n  1107→              │\n  1108→              ▼\n  1109→      session-store shared\n  1110→              │\n  1111→              ▼\n  1112→      realtimeHub.publish()\n  1113→              │\n  1114→              ▼\n  1115→      Both clients receive events\n  1116→```\n  1117→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"edf9e437-5017-45be-933b-2622d1cbfc98","uuid":"6428a45d-c4fd-4e60-99db-5493837edea6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T02:42:07.871Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/wylonyu/selfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/context-snapshot.md","content":"# Context Snapshot for F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n\n## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n\n**Feature Description (from context):**\n\nWeb 页面与 Telegram 共享同一会话，消息双向实时同步。当前 Web 端使用独立的 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，Telegram 端使用 ai-cli-service.js，两套系统完全隔离。\n\n统一架构：将 Web 端和 Telegram 端的消息路由统一到同一个 session store 和 AI CLI 执行引擎（ai-cli-service.js）；废弃或重构 chat-service.js + codebuddy adapter，使 Web 端也通过 ai-cli-service 执行；统一 session key 映射策略，让 Web 和 Telegram 可以关联到同一个会话。\n\n实时同步：Telegram 端收到的消息和回复实时通过 SSE 推送到 Web 页面；Web 端发送的消息同步转发到 Telegram 对话并在 Bot 中执行；双端同时在线时，两边都能看到完整的对话流。\n\n会话绑定：提供会话绑定机制（如 Web 页面输入 Telegram chat ID 或扫码绑定），确保 Web 连接到正确的 Telegram 会话。\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Web 端和 Telegram 端使用同一个 AI CLI 执行引擎，废弃独立的 codebuddy adapter\n- Web 端发送消息后，Telegram 端和 Web 端同时收到 AI 回复\n- Telegram 端对话内容实时推送到已绑定的 Web 页面\n- Web 页面支持输入 Telegram chat ID 绑定到指定会话\n- 双端同时在线时，对话历史完全一致，无消息丢失\n- Web 端断线重连后自动同步离线期间的消息\n\n## Dependencies (Already Completed)\n\n- F-011 - AI CLI Proxy (completed)\n- F-013 - Session and Context Manager (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2 — Project Structure\n\nTop-level directories:\n```\nsrc/\n├── adapters/        - External service adapters (codebuddy.js)\n├── bot/             - Telegram bot implementation\n├── http/            - HTTP server with SSE\n├── pipeline-infra/  - Dev pipeline execution framework\n├── routes/          - HTTP API endpoints\n├── security/        - Security and permission enforcement\n├── services/        - Core business logic (ai-cli-service.js, chat-service.js, session-store.js, realtime-hub.js)\n└── utils/           - Utility functions\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n\n### root.prizm (L0):\n```\nPRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: nodejs\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src/bot: bot.prizm\n- src/http: http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes: routes.prizm\n- src/security: security.prizm\n- src/services: services.prizm\n- src/utils: utils.prizm\n- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\nRULES:\n- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n```\n\n### src/services.prizm (L1):\n```\nMODULE: src/services\nFILES: index.js, ai-cli-service.js, alert-manager-service.js, alias-store.js, audit-log-service.js, backend-registry.js, chat-queue.js, chat-service.js, command-executor-service.js, commit-service.js, config-service.js, file-service.js, file-watcher-service.js, git-service.js, log-pager.js, output-pager-service.js, pipeline-control-service.js, pipeline-controller.js, plan-ingestion-service.js, realtime-hub.js, scheduled-task-service.js, screenshot-service.js, session-context-service.js, session-store.js, status-aggregator.js, system-exec-service.js, system-monitor-service.js, telegram-pusher.js\nRESPONSIBILITY: Core business logic and state management\nINTERFACES:\n- ai-cli-service: executeAICLI(message, chatId)\n- session-store: get(chatId), set(chatId, data)\n- realtime-hub: broadcast(event, data)\n- chat-service: processMessage(message, session)\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: pino: Logging\n- uses: zod: Validation\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n\n### src/services/chat-service.js (80 lines):\n```javascript\nimport { runCodeBuddy } from '../adapters/codebuddy.js';\nimport { sanitizeInput } from '../security/guard.js';\nimport { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n\nexport function buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId) {\n  const normalizedChannel = String(channel ?? '').trim();\n  const normalizedSessionId = String(sessionId ?? '').trim();\n\n  if (!normalizedChannel) {\n    throw new Error('channel 不能为空。');\n  }\n\n  if (!normalizedSessionId) {\n    throw new Error('sessionId 不能为空。');\n  }\n\n  return {\n    channel: normalizedChannel,\n    sessionId: normalizedSessionId,\n    sessionKey: `${normalizedChannel}:${normalizedSessionId}`\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * @param {Object} params\n * @param {string} params.channel\n * @param {string} params.sessionId\n * @param {string} params.message\n * @param {{ onStatus?: Function, onAssistantChunk?: Function, onAssistantDone?: Function }} [params.realtimeHooks]\n */\nexport async function chatWithSession({ channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks = {} }) {\n  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n\n  return chatQueue.run(session.sessionKey, async () => {\n    const sanitized = sanitizeInput(message);\n\n    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n      stage: 'accepted',\n      channel: session.channel,\n      sessionId: session.sessionId\n    });\n\n    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'user', sanitized);\n\n    const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(session.sessionKey, session.channel);\n\n    realtimeHooks.onStatus?.({\n      stage: 'running',\n      channel: session.channel,\n      sessionId: session.sessionId\n    });\n\n    const reply = await runCodeBuddy(prompt, {\n      onStdoutChunk: (text) => {\n        realtimeHooks.onAssistantChunk?.({\n          text,\n          channel: session.channel,\n          sessionId: session.sessionId\n        });\n      }\n    });\n\n    sessionStore.append(session.sessionKey, 'assistant', reply);\n\n    realtimeHooks.onAssistantDone?.({\n      reply,\n      channel: session.channel,\n      sessionId: session.sessionId\n    });\n\n    return reply;\n  });\n}\n\nexport function resetSession({ channel, sessionId }) {\n  const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n  sessionStore.clear(session.sessionKey);\n}\n```\n\n### src/adapters/codebuddy.js (120 lines):\n```javascript\nimport { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n\nfunction writeEcho(tag, text) {\n  const normalized = String(text ?? '');\n  if (!normalized) {\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const lines = normalized.split(/\\r?\\n/);\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (!line) {\n      continue;\n    }\n    process.stdout.write(`[CodeBuddy:${tag}] ${line}\\n`);\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function runCodeBuddy(prompt, options = {}) {\n  const { onStdoutChunk } = options;\n  const args = ['-p', prompt];\n\n  if (config.codebuddyPermissionFlag) {\n    args.push(config.codebuddyPermissionFlag);\n  }\n\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const child = spawn(config.codebuddyBin, args, {\n      stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n    });\n\n    const startedAt = Date.now();\n    logger.info({ pid: child.pid, bin: config.codebuddyBin, args }, 'CodeBuddy process started');\n\n    let stdout = '';\n    let stderr = '';\n\n    const heartbeat =\n      config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs > 0\n        ? setInterval(() => {\n            const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n            logger.info(\n              {\n                pid: child.pid,\n                elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000),\n                stdoutBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stdout),\n                stderrBytes: Buffer.byteLength(stderr)\n              },\n              'CodeBuddy still running'\n            );\n          }, config.codebuddyHeartbeatMs)\n        : null;\n\n    const timeout =\n      config.requestTimeoutMs > 0\n        ? setTimeout(() => {\n            child.kill('SIGTERM');\n            reject(new Error(`CodeBuddy 执行超时（>${config.requestTimeoutMs}ms）`));\n          }, config.requestTimeoutMs)\n        : null;\n\n    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      const text = chunk.toString();\n      stdout += text;\n\n      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n      }\n\n      if (typeof onStdoutChunk === 'function') {\n        onStdoutChunk(text);\n      }\n    });\n\n    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      const text = chunk.toString();\n      stderr += text;\n\n      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n      }\n    });\n\n    child.on('error', (err) => {\n      if (timeout) {\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\n      }\n      if (heartbeat) {\n        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n      }\n      reject(new Error(`无法启动 CodeBuddy: ${err.message}`));\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code) => {\n      if (timeout) {\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\n      }\n      if (heartbeat) {\n        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n      }\n\n      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n      logger.info(\n        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000) },\n        'CodeBuddy process closed'\n      );\n\n      if (code === 0) {\n        resolve(stdout.trim() || 'CodeBuddy 未返回文本结果。');\n        return;\n      }\n\n      reject(\n        new Error(`CodeBuddy 退出码 ${code}。${stderr ? `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}` : ''}`)\n      );\n    });\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/ai-cli-service.js (564 lines):\n```javascript\n// Key interface: executeAiCli({ sessionId, prompt, hooks, signal, timeoutMs, ... })\n// Returns: Promise<{ output, timedOut, interrupted, elapsedMs, exitCode, stderr }>\n// Hooks: onChunk(text), onHeartbeat(info), onStatus(status)\n\nimport { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\nimport { backendRegistry as defaultBackendRegistry } from './backend-registry.js';\nimport { createHeartbeatManager } from '../utils/heartbeat-manager.js';\n\n// Allow dependency injection for testing\nlet backendRegistry = defaultBackendRegistry;\n\n// ... metrics functions ...\n\n/**\n * @typedef {Object} AiCliExecutionOptions\n * @property {string} sessionId - Session identifier\n * @property {string} prompt - User prompt/input\n * @property {string} [userId] - User ID who initiated the task (for permission checks)\n * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onChunk] - Stream chunk callback (text: string) => void\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onHeartbeat] - Heartbeat callback (info: HeartbeatInfo) => void\n * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (status: string) => void\n * @property {AbortSignal} [signal] - Optional abort signal\n * @property {number} [timeoutMs] - Optional timeout override\n * @property {number} [heartbeatThresholdMs] - Heartbeat threshold override\n * @property {number} [heartbeatIntervalMs] - Heartbeat interval override\n * @property {string} [bin] - Optional binary override (for testing)\n * @property {string[]} [args] - Optional args override (for testing, replaces default args)\n */\n\nexport async function executeAiCli(options) {\n  const {\n    sessionId,\n    prompt,\n    userId,\n    hooks = {},\n    signal,\n    timeoutMs,\n    heartbeatThresholdMs,\n    heartbeatIntervalMs,\n    bin,\n    args: customArgs\n  } = options;\n\n  // Get session-specific backend or use default\n  const sessionBackendName = sessionStore.getCurrentBackend(sessionId);\n  const sessionBackend = sessionBackendName ? backendRegistry.getBackend(sessionBackendName) : null;\n  const effectiveBin = bin || (sessionBackend?.binPath) || config.codebuddyBin;\n  const effectiveTimeoutMs = timeoutMs ?? config.requestTimeoutMs;\n  const effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs = heartbeatThresholdMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatThresholdMs;\n  const effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs = heartbeatIntervalMs ?? config.aiCliHeartbeatIntervalMs;\n  const enableHeartbeat = config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat;\n\n  // Validate backend binary exists if using session backend\n  if (sessionBackendName && !backendRegistry.validateBackend(sessionBackendName)) {\n    const defaultBackend = backendRegistry.getDefaultBackend();\n    const fallbackBin = defaultBackend?.binPath || config.codebuddyBin;\n\n    logger.warn(`Backend \"${sessionBackendName}\" not accessible, falling back to default`);\n\n    // Reset to default backend for this session\n    sessionStore.resetBackend(sessionId);\n\n    return {\n      output: `⚠️ 后端 \"${sessionBackendName}\" 不可用，已切换回默认后端。\\n建议：检查后端配置或使用 /cli reset 重置。`,\n      timedOut: false,\n      interrupted: false,\n      elapsedMs: 0,\n      exitCode: null,\n      stderr: ''\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Use custom args if provided (for testing), otherwise build default args\n  const args = customArgs ?? (() => {\n    const defaultArgs = ['-p', prompt];\n    // Use session backend's permission flag if available, otherwise fallback to config\n    const permissionFlag = sessionBackend?.permissionFlag || config.codebuddyPermissionFlag;\n    if (permissionFlag) {\n      defaultArgs.push(permissionFlag);\n    }\n    return defaultArgs;\n  })();\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    let stdout = '';\n    let stderr = '';\n    let stdoutBytes = 0;\n    let interrupted = false;\n    let timedOut = false;\n    const startedAt = Date.now();\n    const sessionKey = sessionId;\n\n    // Heartbeat manager\n    const heartbeatManager = createHeartbeatManager();\n\n    // Spawn process\n    let child;\n    try {\n      child = spawn(effectiveBin, args, {\n        stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']\n      });\n    } catch (err) {\n      resolve({\n        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n        timedOut: false,\n        interrupted: false,\n        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n        exitCode: null,\n        stderr: ''\n      });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Track process in session store\n    sessionStore.setActiveProcess(sessionKey, {\n      pid: child.pid,\n      startedAt,\n      childProcess: child,\n      interrupted: false,\n      timedOut: false,\n      userId\n    });\n\n    logger.info({\n    pid: child.pid,\n    bin: effectiveBin,\n    backend: sessionBackendName || 'default',\n    args,\n    sessionId\n  }, 'AI CLI process started');\n\n    // Handle process error\n    child.on('error', (err) => {\n      cleanup();\n      resolve({\n        output: `无法启动 AI CLI: ${err.message}\\n建议：检查 CODEBUDDY_BIN 配置是否正确。`,\n        timedOut: false,\n        interrupted: false,\n        elapsedMs: Date.now() - startedAt,\n        exitCode: null,\n        stderr\n      });\n    });\n\n    // Handle stdout\n    child.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      const text = chunk.toString();\n      stdout += text;\n      stdoutBytes += Buffer.byteLength(text);\n\n      // Update session store byte count\n      sessionStore.updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, Buffer.byteLength(text));\n\n      // Echo to console if enabled\n      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n        writeEcho('stdout', text);\n      }\n\n      // Call onChunk hook\n      if (typeof hooks.onChunk === 'function') {\n        hooks.onChunk(text);\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Handle stderr\n    child.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n      const text = chunk.toString();\n      stderr += text;\n\n      if (config.codebuddyEchoStdio) {\n        writeEcho('stderr', text);\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Timeout handler\n    const timeout = effectiveTimeoutMs > 0\n      ? setTimeout(() => {\n          timedOut = true;\n          const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n          if (info) {\n            info.timedOut = true;\n          }\n          child.kill('SIGTERM');\n\n          // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n          setTimeout(() => {\n            if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n              child.kill('SIGKILL');\n            }\n          }, 5000);\n        }, effectiveTimeoutMs)\n      : null;\n\n    // Abort signal handler\n    const onAbort = () => {\n      interrupted = true;\n      const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n      if (info) {\n        info.interrupted = true;\n      }\n      child.kill('SIGTERM');\n\n      // Schedule SIGKILL if process doesn't exit\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        if (sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey)) {\n          child.kill('SIGKILL');\n        }\n      }, 5000);\n    };\n\n    if (signal) {\n      signal.addEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n    }\n\n    // Heartbeat setup\n    if (enableHeartbeat && typeof hooks.onHeartbeat === 'function') {\n      heartbeatManager.start({\n        callback: () => {\n          const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n          hooks.onHeartbeat({\n            elapsedMs,\n            stdoutBytes,\n            status: 'running'\n          });\n        },\n        intervalMs: effectiveHeartbeatIntervalMs,\n        thresholdMs: effectiveHeartbeatThresholdMs\n      });\n    }\n\n    // Cleanup function\n    function cleanup() {\n      if (timeout) {\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\n      }\n      heartbeatManager.stop();\n      sessionStore.clearActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n      if (signal) {\n        signal.removeEventListener('abort', onAbort);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Handle process close\n    child.on('close', (code) => {\n      const elapsedMs = Date.now() - startedAt;\n\n      // Check interrupted/timedOut flags from session store (may be set by interruptAiCli)\n      const storedInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionKey);\n      if (storedInfo) {\n        if (storedInfo.interrupted) {\n          interrupted = true;\n        }\n        if (storedInfo.timedOut) {\n          timedOut = true;\n        }\n      }\n\n      cleanup();\n\n      logger.info(\n        { pid: child.pid, code, elapsedSec: Math.floor(elapsedMs / 1000), sessionId },\n        'AI CLI process closed'\n      );\n\n      // Build output\n      let output = stdout.trim();\n\n      if (interrupted) {\n        output = output || '任务已被用户中断。';\n      } else if (timedOut) {\n        output = output || `任务执行超时（>${effectiveTimeoutMs}ms）。\\n建议：使用 /stop 中断或增加 REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS 配置。`;\n      } else if (code !== 0) {\n        output = output || `AI CLI 退出码 ${code}。`;\n        if (stderr.trim()) {\n          output += `\\n错误信息:\\n${stderr.trim()}`;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Record metrics (T-051)\n      recordMetrics({\n        elapsedMs,\n        stdoutBytes,\n        success: code === 0 && !interrupted && !timedOut,\n        timedOut,\n        interrupted\n      });\n\n      resolve({\n        output: output || 'AI CLI 未返回文本结果。',\n        timedOut,\n        interrupted,\n        elapsedMs,\n        exitCode: code,\n        stderr: stderr.trim()\n      });\n    });\n  });\n}\n\nexport function interruptAiCli(sessionId) {\n  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n\n  if (!processInfo) {\n    return { ok: false, error: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n  }\n\n  const { pid, childProcess } = processInfo;\n\n  try {\n    // Mark as interrupted so close handler knows\n    processInfo.interrupted = true;\n\n    // Send SIGTERM first\n    childProcess.kill('SIGTERM');\n\n    // Schedule SIGKILL as backup\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      const stillRunning = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n      if (stillRunning) {\n        try {\n          childProcess.kill('SIGKILL');\n        } catch {\n          // Process already dead\n        }\n      }\n    }, 5000);\n\n    logger.info({ pid, sessionId }, 'AI CLI process interrupted');\n\n    return { ok: true, pid };\n  } catch (err) {\n    return { ok: false, error: `中断失败: ${err.message}` };\n  }\n}\n\nexport function isAiCliRunning(sessionId) {\n  return sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId) !== null;\n}\n\nexport function getActiveProcessInfo(sessionId) {\n  const info = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n  if (!info) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // Don't expose childProcess to external callers\n  return {\n    pid: info.pid,\n    startedAt: info.startedAt,\n    stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0,\n    userId: info.userId\n  };\n}\n\nexport function canInterruptAiCli(sessionId, requestUserId, isAdminFn) {\n  const processInfo = sessionStore.getActiveProcess(sessionId);\n\n  if (!processInfo) {\n    return { canInterrupt: false, reason: '没有正在执行的任务。' };\n  }\n\n  // Admin can always interrupt\n  if (isAdminFn && isAdminFn(requestUserId)) {\n    return { canInterrupt: true };\n  }\n\n  // Task owner can interrupt\n  const taskUserId = processInfo.userId;\n  if (taskUserId && String(taskUserId) === String(requestUserId)) {\n    return { canInterrupt: true };\n  }\n\n  // Otherwise, permission denied\n  return {\n    canInterrupt: false,\n    reason: '权限不足。只有任务发起者或管理员可以中断任务。'\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### src/services/session-store.js (427 lines):\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-010: File search results state for pagination\n  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n  #commandHistoryBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #envOverridesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #lastActivityBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #userIdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-015: AI CLI Backend Switcher\n  #currentBackendBySessionKey = new Map();\n\n  get(sessionKey) {\n    if (!this.#messagesBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n      this.#messagesBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, []);\n    }\n    return this.#messagesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n  }\n\n  append(sessionKey, role, content) {\n    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n    messages.push({ role, content });\n\n    const maxMessages = config.maxHistoryTurns * 2;\n    if (messages.length > maxMessages) {\n      messages.splice(0, messages.length - maxMessages);\n    }\n  }\n\n  clear(sessionKey) {\n    this.#messagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#commitsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // F-009: Clear cwd and output pages\n    this.#cwdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#outputPagesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // F-010: Clear search results\n    this.#searchResultsBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // F-011: Clear active process\n    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // F-013: Clear session context data\n    this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#userIdBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n    // F-015: Clear backend selection\n    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  }\n\n  toPrompt(sessionKey, channel = 'unknown') {\n    const messages = this.get(sessionKey);\n\n    return [\n      `你正在通过 ${channel} 渠道提供电脑助手服务。`,\n      '请使用自然、简洁、可执行的表达。',\n      '如果用户请求系统操作或截图，明确说明步骤与结果。',\n      '当你产出本地文件（截图/文档）时，必须额外输出独立行：SEND_FILE:<绝对路径>。',\n      '禁止仅输出 @image:xxx 或相对路径；路径必须是绝对路径（例如 /var/folders/... 或 /home/...）。',\n      '以下是最近对话上下文：',\n      ...messages.map((msg) => `${msg.role === 'user' ? '用户' : '助手'}: ${msg.content}`),\n      '请继续回答最后一条用户消息。'\n    ].join('\\n');\n  }\n  // ... other methods for commits, cwd, output, search results, active process, command history, env overrides, session tracking, etc.\n\n  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking methods\n  getActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n    return this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n  }\n\n  setActiveProcess(sessionKey, info) {\n    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, {\n      ...info,\n      stdoutBytes: info.stdoutBytes ?? 0\n    });\n  }\n\n  updateProcessBytes(sessionKey, bytes) {\n    const info = this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n    if (info) {\n      info.stdoutBytes = (info.stdoutBytes ?? 0) + bytes;\n    }\n  }\n\n  clearActiveProcess(sessionKey) {\n    this.#activeProcessBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  }\n\n  // F-013: Session and Context Manager methods\n  touchSession(sessionKey, userId) {\n    const now = Date.now();\n    this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n    if (userId !== undefined) {\n      this.#userIdBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, userId);\n    }\n    // Set creation time if this is a new session\n    if (!this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.has(sessionKey)) {\n      this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, now);\n    }\n  }\n\n  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) {\n    const userId = this.#userIdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n    const createdAt = this.#sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n    const lastActivityAt = this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.get(sessionKey);\n\n    // Return null if session has no tracking data\n    if (!createdAt && !lastActivityAt) {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    return {\n      sessionKey,\n      userId: userId || null,\n      cwd: this.#cwdBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null,\n      envOverrides: { ...this.#envOverridesBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) } || {},\n      commandCount: (this.#commandHistoryBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || []).length,\n      createdAt: createdAt || null,\n      lastActivityAt: lastActivityAt || null,\n      // F-015: Add backend information\n      currentBackend: this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null\n    };\n  }\n\n  getAllSessionKeys() {\n    // Return keys from sessions that have activity tracking\n    return Array.from(this.#lastActivityBySessionKey.keys());\n  }\n\n  getCurrentBackend(sessionKey) {\n    return this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.get(sessionKey) || null;\n  }\n\n  setCurrentBackend(sessionKey, backendName) {\n    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.set(sessionKey, backendName);\n  }\n\n  resetBackend(sessionKey) {\n    this.#currentBackendBySessionKey.delete(sessionKey);\n  }\n}\n\nexport const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\nexport { SessionStore };\n```\n\n### src/services/realtime-hub.js (35 lines):\n```javascript\nclass RealtimeHub {\n  #listenersBySession = new Map();\n\n  subscribe(sessionKey, listener) {\n    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey) ?? new Set();\n    listeners.add(listener);\n    this.#listenersBySession.set(sessionKey, listeners);\n\n    return () => {\n      const current = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n      if (!current) {\n        return;\n      }\n\n      current.delete(listener);\n      if (current.size === 0) {\n        this.#listenersBySession.delete(sessionKey);\n      }\n    };\n  }\n\n  publish(sessionKey, event) {\n    const listeners = this.#listenersBySession.get(sessionKey);\n    if (!listeners || listeners.size === 0) {\n      return;\n    }\n\n    for (const listener of listeners) {\n      listener(event);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nexport const realtimeHub = new RealtimeHub();\n```\n\n### src/routes/api-routes.js (106 lines):\n```javascript\nimport { Router } from 'express';\nimport { buildSessionContext, chatWithSession, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\nimport { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\nimport { executeSystemCommand } from '../services/system-exec-service.js';\n\nfunction writeSseEvent(res, event, payload) {\n  res.write(`event: ${event}\\n`);\n  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n\\n`);\n}\n\nexport function createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }) {\n  const router = Router();\n\n  router.get('/events', (req, res, next) => {\n    try {\n      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.query;\n      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n\n      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');\n      res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');\n      res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');\n      res.flushHeaders?.();\n\n      writeSseEvent(res, 'connected', {\n        ok: true,\n        channel: session.channel,\n        sessionId: session.sessionId\n      });\n\n      const unsubscribe = realtimeHub.subscribe(session.sessionKey, (event) => {\n        writeSseEvent(res, event.type, event.payload);\n      });\n\n      const heartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n        res.write(': ping\\n\\n');\n      }, 20000);\n\n      req.on('close', () => {\n        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n        unsubscribe();\n      });\n    } catch (error) {\n      next(error);\n    }\n  });\n\n  router.post('/chat', async (req, res, next) => {\n    try {\n      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, message } = req.body ?? {};\n      const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n\n      const reply = await chatWithSession({\n        channel,\n        sessionId,\n        message,\n        realtimeHooks: {\n          onStatus: (payload) => {\n            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'status', payload });\n          },\n          onAssistantChunk: (payload) => {\n            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_chunk', payload });\n          },\n          onAssistantDone: (payload) => {\n            realtimeHub.publish(session.sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_done', payload });\n          }\n        }\n      });\n\n      res.json({ ok: true, reply });\n    } catch (error) {\n      next(error);\n    }\n  });\n\n  router.post('/chat/reset', async (req, res, next) => {\n    try {\n      const { channel = 'web', sessionId } = req.body ?? {};\n      resetSession({ channel, sessionId });\n      res.json({ ok: true });\n    } catch (error) {\n      next(error);\n    }\n  });\n\n  return router;\n}\n```\n\n### src/http/server.js (25 lines):\n```javascript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createApiRouter } from '../routes/api-routes.js';\nimport { realtimeHub } from '../services/realtime-hub.js';\n\nexport function createHttpServer({ logger }) {\n  const app = express();\n\n  app.use(express.json({ limit: '2mb' }));\n\n  app.get('/healthz', (_req, res) => {\n    res.json({ ok: true });\n  });\n\n  app.use('/api', createApiRouter({ realtimeHub }));\n  app.use(express.static('public'));\n\n  app.use((error, _req, res, _next) => {\n    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    logger.error({ err: message }, 'HTTP request failed');\n    res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: message });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (partial - key sections related to chat handling):\n```javascript\n// Key parts for context\n\nfunction buildSessionId(ctx) {\n  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n}\n\n// Bot uses ai-cli-service for execution:\nconst result = await executeAiCli({\n  sessionId,\n  prompt,\n  hooks: {\n    onChunk: (text) => {\n      streamPublisher.push(text);\n    },\n    onHeartbeat: config.aiCliEnableHeartbeat ? (info) => {\n      // Send/update heartbeat progress message\n      const elapsedSec = Math.floor(info.elapsedMs / 1000);\n      const progressText = `⏳ 任务执行中... (${elapsedSec}s, ${Math.floor(info.stdoutBytes / 1024)}KB)`;\n\n      // Don't await - fire and forget\n      if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n        ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id, undefined, progressText)\n          .catch(() => {});\n      } else {\n        ctx.reply(progressText)\n          .then((msg) => { lastHeartbeatMsg = msg; })\n          .catch(() => {});\n      }\n    } : undefined,\n    onStatus: (status) => {\n      if (status === 'running') {\n        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n});\n\n// Session key format: `telegram:${sessionId}`\nconst sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n\n// Append user message to session history\nsessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', ctx.message.text);\n\n// Append assistant reply to session history\nsessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', result.output);\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5 — Integration Points\n\n### Current Flow:\n\n**Web Path:**\n1. POST /api/chat with message\n2. buildSessionContext() → sessionKey = \"web:<sessionId>\"\n3. chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() (via adapter)\n4. Uses realtimeHub.publish() for SSE\n\n**Telegram Path:**\n1. bot.on('text') receives message\n2. buildSessionId() → uses ctx.chat.id\n3. sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\"\n4. executeAiCli() directly\n5. Messages appended to sessionStore using sessionKey\n\n### Key Problem:\n- Web and Telegram use different execution engines (codebuddy vs ai-cli)\n- Session keys are isolated per channel (web:123 vs telegram:123)\n- No cross-channel message synchronization\n\n---\n\n## Section 6 — Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\nWeb Client\n  │ POST /api/chat\n  ▼\napi-routes.js → chatWithSession() → runCodeBuddy() → sessionKey=\"web:id\"\n                                            │\n                                            ▼\n                                    session-store (isolated)\n\nTelegram Bot\n  │ on('text')\n  ▼\ntelegram.js → executeAiCli() → sessionKey=\"telegram:id\"\n                            │\n                            ▼\n                        session-store (isolated)\n```\n\n### Target Flow:\n\n```\nWeb Client          Telegram Bot\n  │                      │\n  ▼                      │\nSession Key = telegram:<chatId> (bound)\n  │                      │\n  ├──────────────────────┤\n  │                      │\n  ▼                      ▼\nexecuteAiCli()    executeAiCli()\n  │                      │\n  └──────────────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n      session-store shared\n              │\n              ▼\n      realtimeHub.publish()\n              │\n              ▼\n      Both clients receive events\n```\n","numLines":1117,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1117}}}
